{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A single target host\/port that a network service is running on.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol\/hostname","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol\/port","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol\/priority","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol\/srv_target_ptr-6exkt","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol\/weight"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"anchor":"Instance-Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol\/copy()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol\/free()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol\/getHostname()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol\/getPort()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol\/getPriority()","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol\/getWeight()"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"metadata":{"title":"SrvTargetProtocol","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"protocol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SrvTargetProtocol"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO17SrvTargetProtocolP","roleHeading":"Protocol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SrvTargetProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTarget","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetRef"],"title":"Conforming Types","kind":"relationships","type":"conformingTypes"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SrvTargetProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"text":"PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SRV (service) records are used by some network protocols to provide"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"service-specific aliasing and load-balancing. For example, XMPP"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(Jabber) uses SRV records to locate the XMPP server for a domain;","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"rather than connecting directly to ‘example.com’ or assuming a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"specific server hostname like ‘xmpp.example.com’, an XMPP client"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"would look up the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"xmpp-client"},{"type":"text","text":" SRV record for ‘example.com’, and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"then connect to whatever host was pointed to by that record.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Resolver.lookup_service"},{"type":"text","text":"] or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"Gio.Resolver.lookup_service_async","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] to find the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSrvTarget"},{"text":"s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for a given service. However, if you are simply planning to connect","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the remote service, you can use [class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/NetworkService"},{"type":"text","text":"]’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[iface","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnectable","isActive":true},{"text":"] interface and not need to worry about","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"GSrvTarget","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" at all."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"code":"GSrvTarget","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTarget","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SrvTargetRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/srvtargetprotocol"]}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Resolver":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Resolver","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Resolver","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/resolver","kind":"symbol","title":"Resolver","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Resolver","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The object that handle